# Step 1: Build Docker Image from Your Folder
cd your-folder-name
docker build -t imagename .

# Step 2: Add a Tag
docker tag imagename yourdockerhubusername/imagename:tagname
# Example:
docker tag myapp akshatha123/myapp:v1

# Step 3: Login to Docker Hub
docker login
# OR using access token:
echo YOUR_TOKEN | docker login -u your-username --password-stdin

# Step 4: Push Image to Docker Hub
docker push yourdockerhubusername/imagename:tagname
# Example:
docker push akshatha123/myapp:v1

# Step 5: Verify on Docker Hub
# Go to https://hub.docker.com and check your repository

# Step 6: Push the Code to GitHub
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/docker_demo.git
git push -u origin main

# Step 7: Add Docker Hub Credentials in Jenkins
1. Open Jenkins
2. Manage Jenkins → Credentials → Configure Credentials
3. Add:
   Kind: Username & Password
   ID: dockerhub-creds
   Username: your Docker Hub username
   Password: Docker Hub Access Token

# Step 8: Create Jenkins Pipeline Job
1. Jenkins Dashboard → New Item
2. Select "Pipeline"
3. Configure:
   Pipeline → Pipeline script from SCM
   SCM → Git
   Repo URL → https://github.com/yourusername/docker_demo.git
   Script Path → Jenkinsfile

# Step 9: Build Now (manual)
Click "Build Now" in Jenkins to trigger the pipeline.
